            <noteGrp type="workDesc">
               <note type="description">A series of maxims showing “what cannot be relied upon” in the quest for God. It is popularly known by its variant title R. fī mā lā yuʿawwal ʿalayhi (Treatise on what cannot be relied upon).</note>
               <note type="structure">Structure of Work</note>
               <note type="contentsNote">Note on Contents</note>
            </noteGrp>
            <!-- Stemmatics -->
            <note type="stemmatics">OY lists 14 mss., of which only one can be considered historic: Manisa 1183 (650H, written by a direct disciple of IA). OY claims that Beyazit 3750 was copied from an original but our inspection has failed to confirm this. University A3239 (OY) is actually Iṣṭilāhāt (RG 315).</note>
